---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const updated = "June 19, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Flowdira"
  description="The terms and conditions governing the use of the Flowdira website and our website design, development and AI integration services."
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main" class="legal-page">
    <article class="legal container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="legal__lede">
        These terms govern your use of the Flowdira website and the design,
        development and AI integration services we provide. By using our site or
        engaging us for a project, you agree to the terms below.
      </p>
      <p class="legal__updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <h2>1. Agreement to terms</h2>
      <p>
        Flowdira (“Flowdira”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) operates flowdira.com and
        provides website design, web development and AI integration services.
        These Terms &amp; Conditions form a binding agreement between you and
        Flowdira. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, please do not
        use our website or services.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Our services</h2>
      <p>
        We provide professional services including, but not limited to, UI/UX and
        website design, front-end and full-stack web development, and AI feature
        integration. The specific scope, deliverables, timeline and price of any
        engagement are defined in a separate written proposal or quote agreed
        between you and Flowdira, which forms part of these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Quotes, fees &amp; payment</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Project pricing is provided as a written quote and is valid for the
          period stated within it.
        </li>
        <li>
          Unless agreed otherwise, projects require a deposit before work begins,
          with the balance due on completion or per the agreed milestone schedule.
        </li>
        <li>
          Invoices are payable within the period stated on the invoice. Late or
          unpaid invoices may pause work and delay delivery.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Project scope &amp; revisions</h2>
      <p>
        Each engagement includes the deliverables and revision rounds described in
        the agreed proposal. Work that falls outside the agreed scope — including
        additional features, pages or revision rounds — may be quoted separately
        as additional work.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Client responsibilities</h2>
      <p>
        To deliver on time, we rely on you to provide content, brand assets,
        access credentials, feedback and approvals in a timely manner. Delays in
        providing these may affect the project timeline. You are responsible for
        ensuring that any materials you supply do not infringe the rights of any
        third party.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Intellectual property &amp; ownership</h2>
      <p>
        Upon full payment, ownership of the final, delivered work product transfers
        to you, except for any third-party components, open-source libraries, fonts
        or services that remain subject to their own licences. Flowdira retains the
        right to display non-confidential work in our portfolio and marketing
        materials unless agreed otherwise in writing.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        Our work commonly relies on third-party platforms and services such as
        GitHub, Vercel, Cloudflare, content management systems and AI model
        providers. Your use of those services is governed by their own terms, and
        Flowdira is not responsible for changes, outages, pricing or limitations
        imposed by those providers.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Warranties &amp; disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        We take care to deliver high-quality, well-tested work. However, our
        website and services are provided “as is” without warranties of any kind,
        whether express or implied, including fitness for a particular purpose. We
        do not warrant that the website or any deliverable will be uninterrupted,
        error-free or free of all vulnerabilities.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Flowdira shall not be liable for
        any indirect, incidental or consequential damages arising from the use of
        our website or services. Our total liability for any claim arising out of
        an engagement shall not exceed the total fees paid to us for that
        engagement.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Termination</h2>
      <p>
        Either party may terminate an engagement in writing. On termination, you
        agree to pay for all work completed up to the termination date. Sections of
        these terms that by their nature should survive termination — including
        ownership, liability and governing law — will remain in effect.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by applicable local law. Any disputes will be
        resolved through good-faith negotiation and, where required, the competent
        courts of the relevant jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. The latest version will always
        be available on this page with a revised “last updated” date. Continued use
        of our website or services after changes take effect constitutes acceptance
        of the updated terms.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email us at
        <a href="mailto:contact@flowdira.com">contact@flowdira.com</a>.
      </p>

      <a href="/" class="legal__back">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" width="14" height="14">
          <path
            d="M10 12 6 8l4-4"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.7"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
        Back to home
      </a>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
